Description: There are three different modules: (1) model fitting and selection
             using a set of the most commonly used equations describing developmental 
             responses to temperature helped by already existing R packages ('rTPC') 
             and nonlinear regression model functions from 'nls.multstart' (Padfield et al.
             2021, <doi:10.1111/2041-210X.13585>), with visualization of model 
             predictions to guide ecological criteria for model selection; 
             (2) calculation of suitability thermal limits,
             which consist on a temperature interval delimiting the optimal 
             performance zone or suitability; and (3) climatic data extraction 
             and visualization inspired on previous research (Taylor et al. 2019,
             <doi:10.1111/1365-2664.13455>), with either exportable rasters, 
             static map images or html, interactive maps.
